text:
*@everyone*

I have created a private app, configured an API Key, and oAuth token,
granted the 'content' scope to the private app, and using its oAuth token to make an API call
to get all blog posts
<https://developers.HubSpot.com/docs/api/cms/blog-post>

But I am still getting the following error in response
```HTTP 403

{
  "category": "MISSING_SCOPES",
  "correlationId": "8f876add-1bb5-4e1b-8667-996b8fbda7ac",
  "errors": [
    {
      "context": {
        "requiredScopes": [
          "content"
        ]
      },
      "message": "All of the following scopes are required."
    }
  ],
  "links": {
    "scopes": "<https://developers.HubSpot.com/scopes>"
  },
  "message": "This app hasn't been granted all required scopes to make this call. Read more about required scopes here: <https://developers.HubSpot.com/scopes>.",
  "status": "error"
}```
